With department chair approval, students may pursue a course of study which meets their individual needs and interests. Must be initiated early and all courses must be pre-approved. ICS consists of 18-20 units with at least one course at the 300-400 level. Courses selected by student in consultation with an advising faculty member. The list of courses is a contract between the student and the department.
